JOB DESCRIPTION for SUPERINTENDENT in Hunts Point (Bronx):<br>
<br>
Our property management company is looking to hire a Superintendent for a building by Hunts Point in the Bronx. The property consists of approximately 15 units and the position is a long term position.<br>
<br>
Candidate must be 39-54 years old.<br>
<br>
Candidate must have maintenance experience such as basic electric, plumbing, painting and HVAC. Candidate must be a well organized individual to fulfill a full-time Superintendent position. The ideal candidate will be extremely friendly, helpful, knowledgeable and able to multi-task. Candidate must be particularly confident in their communication skills and abilities to remain keenly calm and organized at all times when helping with building needs. <br>
<br>
Major Duties and Responsibilities:<br>
<br>
â¢Performs handyman, porter and seasonal worker duties.<br>
â¢Ensures compliance and adherence to building rules and regulations. <br>
â¢Examines boiler by testing safety valves and performing routine maintenance.<br>
â¢Cleans public spaces daily including the front of the building, yards, stairway, entrance hall, hallways, lobby entrance, roof inspection and roof cleaning, etc.<br>
â¢Performs minor repairs and adjustments to various appliances when needed.<br>
â¢Maintains appliances and equipment.<br>
â¢Is able to use a variety of equipment such as vacuum cleaners, floor polishers, ladders, mops, brooms, cleaning accessories, plumbing wrenches, screwdrivers, step ladders, etc.<br>
â¢Handles urgent or minor complaints and emergency situations as they arise<br>
â¢Ensures that fire escapes and passages leading to them are clear of obstructions.<br>
â¢Performs daily waste disposal to make sure building is organized and free of trash.<br>
â¢Ensures adherence to city regulations regarding waste removal.<br>
<br>
Work hours: <br>
<br>
The building Superintendent is expected to be on-site Monday through Friday between 8 a.m. and 8 p.m. During these hours Super is expected to maintain the building including cleaning hallways, stairways, building entrance, disposal chute rooms, disposing of all waste, maintaining the boiler and heating systems and attending to residents in need. In case of snow and ice obstructions Super needs to remove all snow and ice from all appropriate passage ways surrounding the building during winter time. <br>
<br>
All other hours:<br>
<br>
Superintendent is to be "on-call" and respond to emergencies and other building needs 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. The super must be reachable at all times via mobile telephone and readily available to work at all times. Super must be available to speak to property manager at all times.<br>
<br>
*Compensation:*<br>
<br>
Super will receive a set weekly salary depending on his qualifications agreed upon when hired. <br>
<br>
Education and Experience Requirements:<br>
 <br>
â¢Must have a High School diploma or GED<br>
â¢Must have similar work experience of 3+ years or more<br>
â¢Must have the ability to communicate in English and Spanish<br>
â¢Must have excellent people skills<br>
â¢Must be able to pass a criminal background check<br>
<br>
*If you're interested, please reply with your resume with at least 3 (three) references from jobs you have worked in for 2 (two) years or more and a short paragraph as to why this position is ideal (in terms of qualifications and schedule) for you.<br>
<br>
ONLY serious and qualified candidates please.    </section>

